Project Summary
This is a Hoare Logic verification tool — a Python-based academic assignment implementing program correctness verification using formal methods.

What it does
The project implements two core algorithms from Hoare Logic:

Weakest Precondition (wprec) — Given a program command c and a postcondition q, computes the weakest precondition wp(c, q): the minimal assumption needed about the initial state to guarantee q holds after c executes.

Verification Condition Generation (VC / VCG) — Given a pre/postcondition and a program, generates a set of logical proof obligations that, if all valid, prove the program correct with respect to its specification.

The generated verification conditions can then be discharged automatically using the Z3 SMT solver (optional).

Architecture
